Step 1: Calculate the Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities (current liabilities) = 1,124,588.25  
• Total Owner's Equity = 14,163,543.07  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
  = 1,124,588.25 / 14,163,543.07  
  ≈ 0.08  

Step 2: Calculate the Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 1,163,543.07 and Total Revenue = 5,991,764.34  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (1,163,543.07 / 5,991,764.34) × 100%  
  ≈ 19.41%  

Step 3: Calculate the Return on Assets (ROA)  
• Total Assets at period end = 15,288,131.32  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%  
  = (1,163,543.07 / 15,288,131.32) × 100%  
  ≈ 7.61%  

Step 4: Calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• Accounts Receivable at period end = 1,133,414.13; the initial value at the beginning is 0  
• We use the average accounts receivable = (Beginning + Ending) / 2  
  = (0 + 1,133,414.13) / 2  
  = 566,707.07  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 5,991,764.34 / 566,707.07  
  ≈ 10.57  

Thus, the solution in the required JSON format is:
 
{"solution": {"Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.08", "Net Profit Margin": "19.41%", "Return on Assets (ROA)": "7.61%", "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "10.57"}}
